Method Detail

hasNext

boolean hasNext()
Returns true if the iteration has more elements. (In other words, returns true if next would return an element rather than throwing an exception.)

Returns:
true if the iterator has more elements.

next

IDataSegmentIterator.IDataSegmentChunk next(int chunkSize)
Returns the next element with the given size (in bytes) in the iteration. Calling this method repeatedly until the hasNext() method returns false will return each element in the underlying collection exactly once.

Parameters:
chunkSize - The requested size of the next data segment chunk.
Returns:
the next chunk in the iteration.
